                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War 1939/1032: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-04T23:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 4, 1943—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 6—12:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1351. I have learned from reliable source that the Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    shortly after his return to Istanbul yesterday saw the Swedish, Swiss, Spanish
                    and Portuguese diplomatic representatives in succession and thereafter sent for
                    the Italian Chargé d’Affaires.</p>
                <p>I am inclined to the view that these visits were in connection with contemplated
                    concerted action by the neutrals in respect of the American, British and Soviet
                    notes concerning refuge to war criminals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
